ng or ruling out the suspected diagnosis.<ref name=\"Tang\"/>\n\nIn dermatology, every textbook feature of a lesion need not be be present to make the diagnosis.<ref name=pcds>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pcds.org.uk/p/skin-disease-examination|title=Examination {{!}} Primary Care Dermatology Society {{!}} UK|last=|first=|date=|website=www.pcds.org.uk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> Likewise, in cardiology, the expectation to explain every change on an [[ECG]] to conclude a diagnosis may represent diagnostic greed.<ref name=Platosnous>{{Cite web|url=http://platosnous.com/main-blog/2015/10/24/sin-of-ecg-interpretation|title=Borkmann's Point and Diagnostic Greed|website=Plato's Nous|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> Another example has been of [[lead poisoning]] where toxicology results have failed to support the diagnosis despite other features of heavy metal poisoning being present.<ref name=Ballardie>{{Cite journal|last=Ballardie|first=Francis|last2=Cowley|first2=Richard|last3=Cox|first3=Alan|last4=Curry|first4=Alan|last5=Denley|first5=Helen|last6=Denton|first6=John|last7=Dick|first7=Jeremy|last8=Guerquin-Kern|first8=Jean-Luc|last9=Redmond|first9=Anthony|date=2009-02-14|title=Did he really bring the war home with him? \u2013 Authors' reply|url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(09)60197-5/abstract|journal=The Lancet|language=English|volume=373|issue=9663|pages=543|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(09)60197-5|issn=0140-6736}}</ref>\n\nArguments for the need, on occasion, to have diagnostic greed, have also been made.<ref name=King>{{Cite book|last=King|first=Mary D.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2NGNEJSEiGcC&pg=PA117|title=A Handbook of Neurological Investigations in Children|last2=Stephenson|first2=John B. P.|date=2009|publisher=Mac Keith Press|chapter=2.9. Microscopic examination: Cells and biopsies|isbn=978-1-898683-69-8|location=|pages=117|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Medical terminology]]\n\n{{Med-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: be be \u2192 be", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnostic_greed"}
